[normal] The abandoned 2008 residence test would not 
[normal]have 
[normal]excluded EU nationals from accessing legal aid (regardless of where 
[normal]they are resident) or others covered by reciprocal arrangements. It would not have affected cases concerning immigration issues (about entry or terms of stay), nor the detention of any client under the Mental 
[normal]Heath
[normal] Act 1983, nor childcare or supervision pr
[normal]oceedings under the Children Act 1989, nor child abduction proceedings covered by the Hague Convention, nor domestic violence proceedings, and nor would it cover housing proceedings where the client was at risk of homelessness. The 2008 consultation paper 
[normal]accepted, without much elaboration, that it would not be 
[normal]‘appropriate’
[normal] to leave work of this kind unfunded.
